02/03/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Giovanni Di Stasi, president of the Council of Europe (CoE) Congress of Local and Regional Authorities, praised on Wednesday (1 March) Turkey's first steps in the decentralisation effort, urging further efforts and continued political will to "create a modern democracy".
Di Stassi was addressing the SIGMA Conference on Public Administration Reform and Territorial Organisation, held in Ankara.
Also Wednesday, the head of the Turkish Supreme Board of Radio and Television, Zahit Akman, announced that four regional TV networks have been allowed to start broadcasting Kurdish-language programmes this month.
The state media watchdog recently decided to allow private regional media to broadcast in Kurdish.
(NTV - 02/03/06;
CoE Web site - 01/03/06)
